-- Jamaica’s Cabinet Approves Water Contract for Kingston Upgrades
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2012-09-14T12:35:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-14/jamaica-s-cabinet-approves-water-contract-for-kingston-upgrades.html
Jamaica’s cabinet approved an $18
million contract with Kier Construction Ltd. for water system
upgrades in Kingston and St. Andrew that include new pumping
equipment, supply transmission lines and wastewater treatment.  Government minister Sandrea Falconer said 26 sites in the
Kingston area will see upgrades to the water network such as the
installation of chlorination facilities and structural work on
at least three reservoirs near the capital.  Funding for the projects will come from the government as
well as the  Inter-American Development Bank .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Hackley in Zurich at 
